{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
It’s [C]about thirty years when [F]I courted [C]and married
Armanda Gilbraith I’d soon call my [G]wife
My brother he [C]stabbed me [F]for some [C]unknown reason
Just [C]three month’s later I’d taken Tom’s life
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
I [C]was  captured and tried in [F]the village [C]of Kingston
Not a man in that county would speak one kind [G]word
When the [C]jury came in with [F]the verdict [C]next mornin’
